<thisCommand> [<-|+ip> <duration> <reason>]

Will ban a user from the network based on their ip address.

If no args are specified, a list of Z-lines are shown. (The same can be done by doing /STATS z.)

Note: This command can only be used by IRC operators.

Example(s):
---------------
/<thisCommand>
/<thisCommand> -8.8.8.8 1 Removing
/<thisCommand> +127.0.0.1 3600 Take a timeout.

Footnotes:
----------
1. The duration cannot be zero, even when removing.
